Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Parts of David ben Abraham Maimuni's homiletico-agadic commentary on Leviticus.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 29; written lines: 29; Catchwords on every page. Chapter titles given in larger square letters. Regular mastara ruling. Running titles on every page.

binding.p: BM in-house. Black buckram, blind-tooled. Spine title: 'David ben Abraham. Comm. on Leviticus. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 69.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: A. C. Reichardt: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 June 1867: inscribed, folio [97v].
